==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|stiffenes}}; equivalent to {{suffix|en|stiff|ness}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~|es}}

# [[rigidity|Rigidity]] or a measure of rigidity.
# [[inflexibility|Inflexibility]] or a measure of inflexibility.
# [[inelegance|Inelegance]]; a lack of [[relaxedness]].
#: {{ux|en|His '''stiffness''' hampered the conversation.}}
#* '''1699''', {{w|Sir William Temple, 1st Baronet|William Temple}}, ''[http://essays.quotidiana.org/temple/heads_for_conversation/ Heads designed for an essay on conversations]''
#*: Study gives strength to the mind; conversation, grace: the first apt to give '''stiffness''', the other suppleness: one gives substance and form to the statue, the other polishes it.
# [[muscular|Muscular]] [[tension]] due to unaccustomed or excessive exercise or work; [[soreness]].

